title: [Angargreft, Burrow]
description: Overhead, the ceiling of the hall is a twisted fusion of stone archway and draping, oozing silk.  The stuff drips down over a pile of dull scales that litter the ragged floor around a worm's shed husk.  Greying and brittle, the remnants are immense in length, hinting at a truly colossal source.
paths: Obvious exits: north, east, southeast, south, northwest
